    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>sugar </strong>and cook for 3 min, or until starting to soften, then add your <strong>mince</strong> and cook for a further 4-5 min, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p><p>(Doubled your protein? Use 2 pans!)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/double-lean-beef-keema-with-lime-and-coriander/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, top, tail, peel and chop your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> into small, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and grate (or finely chop) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Peel and grate (or finely chop) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Tip: Take the mince off the heat if you need longer to chop to avoid burning!</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/double-lean-beef-keema-with-lime-and-coriander/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>carrot</strong>, <strong>grated ginger</strong> and <strong>grated garlic</strong> to the pan and cook for 1 min</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/double-lean-beef-keema-with-lime-and-coriander/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>beef stock mix</strong>,<strong> tomato paste</strong> and<strong> curry powder </strong>into the pan and give everything a good mix up</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/double-lean-beef-keema-with-lime-and-coriander/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Stir your <strong>basmati rice</strong> into the pan</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/double-lean-beef-keema-with-lime-and-coriander/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> to the pan and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until the mince is cooked through (no pink meat!), the rice is cooked and the water has been absorbed</p><p>Check and stir occasionally to prevent the rice from sticking to the bottom</p><p>Tip: Add a splash of water if the rice looks a little dry!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/double-lean-beef-keema-with-lime-and-coriander/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks (save some leaves for garnish!)</p><p>Stir the <strong>chopped coriander</strong> and juice of <strong>half</strong> your <strong>lime[s]</strong> through the cooked rice \u2013 this is your <strong>keema</strong></p><p>Taste for seasoning, adding more <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> if needed</p><p>Chop the <strong>remaining lime[s]</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/double-lean-beef-keema-with-lime-and-coriander/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> keema</strong> in a bowl</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>reserved coriander leaves </strong>and a <strong>lime wedge</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
